The United Arab Emirates (UAE) have reported successfully intercepting two ballistic missiles launched by the Yemeni Houthi fighters. The projectiles were destroyed by air defense forces, with debris falling in various parts of the capital Abu Dhabi, the defense ministry reported, as cited by the state news agency WAM. The moment of the early Monday-morning incident was filmed from the ground by multiple witnesses, according to purported footage of the incident circulating on social media. ðŸ‡¦ðŸ‡ª NEW - Video of UAE air defences launching to intercept a missile attack in the vicinity of Al Shahama area of Abu Dhabi, UAE. pic.twitter.com/uKxp6ExVCzâ€” Alex Tiffin (@RespectIsVital) January 24, 2022 ðŸ‡¦ðŸ‡ª NEW - Video of UAE air defences launching to intercept a missile attack in the vicinity of Al Shahama area of Abu Dhabi, UAE. pic.twitter.com/uKxp6ExVCz ðŸ‡¦ðŸ‡ª UAE | 2 Ballistic Missile Intercepted The UAE intercepted two ballistic missiles aimed at Abu Dhabi early Monday, according to its state-run news agency, the latest strike on the Emirati capital.#UAEpic.twitter.com/ybe0ZOaTYfâ€” The RAGE X (@theragex) January 24, 2022 ðŸ‡¦ðŸ‡ª UAE | 2 Ballistic Missile Intercepted The UAE intercepted two ballistic missiles aimed at Abu Dhabi early Monday, according to its state-run news agency, the latest strike on the Emirati capital.#UAEpic.twitter.com/ybe0ZOaTYf Shortly after the interceptor missiles were launched, what appeared to be burning debris could be seen falling down. New footage of ballistic missiles interception by air defenses over Abu Dhabi, UAE pic.twitter.com/GN9W0czeTVâ€” Insider Paper (@TheInsiderPaper) January 24, 2022 New footage of ballistic missiles interception by air defenses over Abu Dhabi, UAE pic.twitter.com/GN9W0czeTV The thwarted attack briefly disrupted traffic at the Abu Dhabi International Airport. There were no casualties or damage reported on the ground. The Houthi rebels would not immediately claim responsibility for the missile launch